  <front>
   <head>A NURSERY LESSON (DEVOTIONAL).</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">, little child, who gives to thee</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thy life and limbs, so light and free?</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thy moving eyes to look around,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thy ears to catch the softest sound?</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thy food and clothing, friends and home?</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Tis God from whom those blessings come;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And what shouldst thou do? canst thou guess?</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To prove to Him thy thankfulness</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For life and friends, for clothes and food? â€”</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+" line_length="2">"Be good."</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And tell me, little-one, I pray,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Who gives thee pleasure in thy play?</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Who makes the happy girl and boy</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To run, and leap, and shout for joy,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When looking on the clear blue sky;</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The clouds, that float, the birds that fly;</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Trees, flowers, and every pretty thing?</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Tis God from whom those blessings spring;</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And in return what shouldst thou do?</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">"Be good, and love Him too."</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
